    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-03-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-03-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="109"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d109">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">574.D1/18</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Chargé</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lindsay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-03-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1920</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 136</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to Mr. Lansing’s note of February
                        10th<note n="85" xml:id="d109fn85">See footnote 84, <ref target="#pg_111">p.
                            111</ref>.</note> extending to His Majesty’s Government an invitation to
                    send representatives to Washington for a Preliminary Conference on the subject
                    of International Communications, I have the honour to inform you, by direction
                    of my Government, that they would be glad to have as soon as possible a list of
                    the specific proposals which it is intended to place on the agenda for a
                    Preliminary Meeting of this kind.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">R. C. Lindsay</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
